ed as a Lieutenant in the American Revolutionary War while his older brother Selah Hart rose to General in the Connecticut Militia — captured by the British in September 1776 during the New York retreat. Both were sons of Nathaniel Hart × Abigail Hooker, 4th-generation descendants of Thomas Hooker. Noadiah served through the war, became a Deacon in the Harwinton church by 1804, and died in Southington in 1817 at 80.","number":1},{"number":2,"category":"religion","header":"Deacon of Harwinton church; lived to 80","body":"After the war, he became Deacon of the church in Harwinton in 1804, removed to Southington, and lived in his daughter Velina's household near her mill — a site later covered by the \"Plant Ponds.\" He died in 1817 at age 80, the longest-lived of the three brothers."}],"cross_connections":[],"military_service":[{"war":"American Revolutionary War","rank":"Lieutenant","side":"American","unit":"Connecticut Militia","battles":[],"war_id":"WAR004"}],"bio":{"display_name":"Lt. Noadiah Hart","first_name":"Noadiah","last_name":"Hart","title":"Lieutenant","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"slug":"noadiah-hart-1737"},"X01030":{"id":"X01030","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":[],"sources":[],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H00275","children_ids":["H00565","H00566","H00567","H00567a","H00568","H00569"],"end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1785,"date_year":1760,"date_month":11,"date_day":20,"location_city":"Farmington","location_state":"Connecticut"}],"parents":{},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"birth":{},"death":{},"cross_co